  n = len(nums)\n        \n        for i in range(n - 1, 1, -1):\n            left, right = 0, i - 1\n            while left < right:\n                if nums[left] + nums[right] > nums[i]:\n                    count += right - left\n                    right -= 1\n                else:\n                    left += 1\n        \n        return count\n```\n\nThis solution sorts the input array and uses a two-pointer technique to efficiently count the number of valid triplets that can form a triangle. The time complexity of this solution is O(n^2), which is efficient given the constraints.", "estimated_date": 1438905600000}